The paper deals with the challenges of multimedia information retrieval and understanding, specifically in modeling concept semantics in context. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) or Computation and Language (cs.CL) sub-categories. The use of a Siamese architecture for modeling contextualized semantics also suggests that the paper could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with image and music datasets, which suggests that it could also belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) or Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
